      ],
      "source": "https://coxsackie.org/history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The town’s name comes from a Native American word meaning “owl’s hoot,” a phrase still used by locals.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coxsackie%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Coxsackie was incorporated as a town in 1788, just a decade after the American Revolution ended.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3,
        8
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2",
        "Wikipedia"
